17\/safe-as-long-as-silent\/","url_meta":{"origin":35377,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Silence: You are safe as long as you stay silent","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 17, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Mu\u2019adh ibn Jabal reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, you will continue to be safe as long as you remain silent. If you speak, it will be recorded for you or against you.\u201d Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Kab\u012br lil-\u1e6cabar\u0101n\u012b 20\/73 Grade: Hasan li ghayrihi (fair due to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":41396,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/10\/05\/speak-no-evil\/","url_meta":{"origin":35377,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Silence: Allah has mercy on those who speak no evil","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 5, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Khalid ibn Abi \u2018Imran reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would hold his tongue for a long time. Then, the Prophet said, \u201cI fear for you because of this. May Allah have mercy on a servant who speaks goodness and is rewarded, or he refrains from speaking\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11985,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/02\/02\/most-sins-lisan-kalam\/","url_meta":{"origin":35377,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Speech: Most sins committed by the tongue","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 2, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cMost of the sins of the children of Adam are on their tongues.\u201d Ibn Mas'ud said, \"O tongue! Speak goodness and be rewarded, or remain silent and be safe, lest you become regretful.\" Source: al-Mu\u2019jam\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26443,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/05\/21\/iman-haya-speaking-less\/","url_meta":{"origin":35377,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Haya: Modesty, speaking less are branches of faith","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 21, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Umamah reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cModesty and reticence are two branches of faith. Profanity and temerity are two branches of hypocrisy.\u201d Imam al-Tirmidhi commented, \u201cReticence is to speak little. Profanity is to speak obscenely. Temerity is to speak too often, such as those\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23930,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/10\/27\/ibn-umar-hated-cursing\/","url_meta":{"origin":35377,"position":5},"title":"Ibn Umar on Curses: Most hated people to Allah curse often","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 27, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Qatadah reported: Ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cVerily, the most hateful of servants to Allah is every transgressor, cursing others.\u201d Source: al-Zuhd wal-Raqa\u0304\u2019iq 666 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0627\u062f\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0652\u063a\u064e\u0636\u064e \u0639\u0650\u0628\u064e\u0627\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0643\u064f\u0644\u0651\u064f \u0637\u064e\u0639\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064d \u0644\u064e\u0639\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064d 666 \u0627\u0644\u0632\u0647\u062f \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0631\u0642\u0627\u0626\u0642 \u0644\u0627\u0628\u0646\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/35377","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=35377"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/35377\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.